      • decodeHexRGB

        public static java.awt.Color decodeHexRGB(java.lang.String rgb)
        This is the same as Color.decode(String) except that it does NOT throw a NumberFormatException, but instead returns null if decoding fails.
        Parameters:
        rgb - An HTML color string with or without a # or 0x prefix, e.g.: #FF00FF, FF00FF, or 0xFF00FF
        Returns:
        A color if the rgb value is valid or null otherwise.
